<Layout title="Advisory">
  <h1>Advisory</h1>

  <p>
    Alongside my research, I advise government bodies, think tanks, and NGOs on
    problems at the intersection of AI capability and information integrity.
    Engagements are scoped narrowly around a specific risk or decision, drawing
    directly on my published research rather than general consulting practice.
  </p>

  <h2>Engagement types</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>FIMI analysis</strong> — assessing foreign information
      manipulation and interference campaigns: detection methodology, evidence
      review, and characterization of tactics.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Threat and vulnerability assessment</strong> — evaluating where an
      organization's information environment or AI systems are exposed to
      manipulation, misuse, or failure.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Agentic AI adoption</strong> — independent technical review of
      where agentic AI systems are and aren't trustworthy for a given use case,
      grounded in what the underlying models can be shown to do.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
  <p>
    Government bodies, think tanks, NGOs, and technical teams who need an
    independent researcher's assessment rather than a vendor's pitch — and who
    value being told what the evidence actually supports.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    The best starting point is a short email describing the problem:{' '}
    <a href="mailto:tim.niven.public@gmail.com">tim.niven.public@gmail.com</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
